Juanflaco wrote:Unfortunately, I didn't get much information about the final confrontation. The dispatch manager did indicate that the driver offered to bring the phone to me if I wanted to pay him to drop it off. LOL. This was the first time I told the manager that I was actually back home and running the operation from a situation room in MT. Goddamn I just wanted to say it, you know? He laughed his ass off and said he'd personally drop the phone at airport lost & found, where I have an incident open and they were notified to expect it. Based on the evidence above, I have to think the driver knew he had it.I realize I'm not quite out of the woods yet, I need to call Lost & Found this morning to confirm they have it and figure out how to get it back. The final GPS update I received was sent last night and shows the phone just outside terminal 1, so this appears to have been sent as the dispatch manager was returning it to the terminal. The phone isn't currently responding to location requests so we're flying blind from here on out!I'd have offered to pay the guy to ship the phone directly back to you. Hopefully after all this work you still don't end up without your phone, now that it's been deposited in the ether of airport lost and found.
