Particularly with the GPS running. To get position reports that accurate it must have been using GPS, not just tower triangulation. I don't know about the droid but on my GPS-enabled phones the GPS sucks the battery dry in about two hours - and that's without sending position reports. Maybe Plan B is clever enough to only turn the GPS on every so often?
Juanflaco
Ars Tribunus Militum
Tribus: Big Sky Country
Registered: Jul 25, 2003Posts: 2160
Posted: Mon Aug 01, 2011 3:29 pm
DriverGuru wrote:Particularly with the GPS running. To get position reports that accurate it must have been using GPS, not just tower triangulation. I don't know about the droid but on my GPS-enabled phones the GPS sucks the battery dry in about two hours - and that's without sending position reports. Maybe Plan B is clever enough to only turn the GPS on every so often?Yes, I believe it only activates GPS when it receives the keyworded text message. Reviewing my Google voice history I see that I requested its location 42 times. Following the first successful request I received a single notification email followed by 6 position update emails of increasing accuracy, spanning a total time of 9 minutes. If GPS were active that entire time I can't imagine those 42 requests would have been facilitated with the remaining charge on the phone, which had to have been below 75% when I lost it.Protip: don't hammer the location requests like I did; your thief might not be courteous enough to keep the phone charged for you!
