I have to mention - not all cabbies would have been so, um, casual in their approach to returning the phone. My biz partner and I were in NYC once to deliver a custom seminar to a major client. I had to carry THREE laptops in two laptop bags. The first evening after setup, we cabbed it back to the hotel and between being distracted in convo with him, and the long-ingrained habit of carrying just one laptop bag, I left the other one - my main laptop - in the cab. This cabbie didn't just have a lead foot. He moved that cab as if it had a NOx bottle. By the time I realized I was short one bag he was around the next corner. This was at about 10 pm. About 2 am the front desk called me. He'd come back with the laptop. He said he hadn't noticed the bag (black bag, black cab interior) but his next fare did - and that was a long one and he had another one before he could get back to the hotel. But bring it back, he did. I tipped him pretty heavily!
